name: la_forge
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "la_forge" %}
{% set version = "1.0.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0f27c3ecd7c887f4b027d65b94bebfb52da1c6c2b083ae1784d24797f7815366

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - numpy >=1.16
    - scipy >=1.0.0
    - matplotlib-base >=2.0.0
    - astropy >=3.0
    - corner
    - six
    - h5py >=3.4.0

test:
  imports:
    - la_forge
    - la_forge.diagnostics
    - la_forge.core
    - la_forge.gp
    - la_forge.rednoise
    - la_forge.slices
    - la_forge.utils

about:
  home: https://github.com/nanograv/la_forge
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Pulsar Timing Array Bayesian Data Visualization
  description: |
    Python package for conveniently plotting results from pulsar timing array bayesian analyses. Many of the functions are best used with enterprise outputs.
  doc_url: https://la-forge.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/nanograv/la_forge

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - Hazboun6
    - AaronDJohnson
